level 0
keywords REMORT ADEPT
---
@@aREMORT@@W
Your @@yfirst@@W remort class requires the matching mortal
pre-requisite class at @@y100@@W.
Your @@ysecond@@W remort class requires:
  - your first remort class at @@y100@@W,
  - all mortal classes at @@y100@@W, and
  - the matching mortal pre-requisite class for that second remort
    at @@y100@@W.
When you are ready to remort, type gain <class shorthand shown below>.
Remort classes and mortal pre-requisites are:
        -@@pSorcerer@@W [@@ySor@@W] (Magi)
        -@@WWizard@@W [@@yWiz@@W] (Magi)
        -@@aPaladin@@W [@@yPal@@W] (Cleric)
        -@@CPriest@@W [@@yPri@@W] (Cleric)
        -@@dAssassin@@W [@@yAss@@W] (Cipher)
        -@@dWarlock@@W [@@yWlk@@W] (Cipher)
        -@@cKnight@@W [@@yKni@@W] (Warden)
        -@@cSwordsman@@W [@@ySwo@@W] (Warden)
        -@@GNecromancer@@W [@@yNec@@W] (Psionicist)
        -@@mEgomancer@@W [@@yEgo@@W] (Psionicist)
        -@@gMonk@@W [@@yMon@@W] (Pugilist)
        -@@gBrawler@@W [@@yBra@@W] (Pugilist)

@@aADEPT@@W
Adept classes are a third tier of progression beyond remort. To unlock
adepts, you must have at least @@y2@@W remort classes at level @@y100@@W.
Each adept class requires one of its matching remort classes at @@y100@@W.
When you are ready to adept, type gain <class shorthand shown below>.
Adept classes and their remort pre-requisites are:
        -@@pGrand Magi@@W [@@yGra@@W] (Sorcerer or Wizard)
        -@@aTemplar@@W [@@yTem@@W] (Paladin or Priest)
        -@@dNightblade@@W [@@yNig@@W] (Assassin or Warlock)
        -@@cCrusader@@W [@@yCru@@W] (Knight or Swordsman)
        -@@GKinetimancer@@W [@@yKin@@W] (Necromancer or Egomancer)
        -@@gMartial Artist@@W [@@yMar@@W] (Monk or Brawler)
